'''Carrot and stick''' is a term sometimes mistakenly used to refer to a notion of rewarding good behaviour while simultaneously punishing bad behaviour. This is a confusion of the concept of "Reward OR Punishment" which must of course be an OPTION (one or the other). To use both simultaneously would be fruitless and self-defeating. This interpretation of "carrot and stick" is therefore WRONG and should be ignored.

The term in fact is a classic metaphor providing a visual image of a donkey being expected by its rider to walk constantly towards a carrot which is suspended (just out of reach of the donkey's mouth) from a stick held by the donkey's rider (much as an angler would dangle bait to catch fish). The implication overall is that the rider is a bigger simpleton than the donkey.